  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>ciabatta<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;into bite-sized cubes</p>\r\n<p>Add them to one end of the baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>almonds</strong> to the other end and set the tray aside</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong>over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chicken thigh fillets</strong>, season them in the pan with a big pinch of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 4 min, turning once or until browned</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;browned, cover with a lid, reduce the heat to low and cook for a further 2 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, place the<strong> ciabatta</strong> and<strong> almonds</strong> in the warmed oven for 10 min or until both are starting to lightly brown</p>\r\n<p>Once browned, set the tray aside to cool</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>mayonnaise</strong> with the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>&ndash;<strong>&nbsp;</strong>this is your <strong>wholegrain mayo dressing<strong>&nbsp;</strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Shred or tear the <strong>little gem lettuce<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces,&nbsp;add them to a large mixing bowl and set aside&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Quarter the<strong> apple</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong>&nbsp;</span>(skins on)&nbsp;and cut into cubes, discarding the core<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>celery</strong> finely&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Trim then slice the <strong>spring onion</strong><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>apple</strong>, <strong>celery</strong> and <strong>spring onion</strong> to the salad bowl&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/392_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>chicken thigh fillets</strong> are cooked through, transfer them to a clean chopping board and leave to cool for around 2-4 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Shred<strong>&nbsp;</strong>the rested<strong> chicken</strong> with&nbsp;two forks, tearing the meat up &ndash; this is known as 'pulling'</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
